      "id": "h2",
      "label": "Topology Regime Flip Test (primary test)",
      "statement": "MEK1 mean PRISM LFC < mTOR mean PRISM LFC within KRAS Chronos < -0.5 colorectal lines. Equivalently: MEK inhibitors kill KRAS-dependent CRC cells more effectively than mTOR inhibitors. This is the topology regime shift test: In D3_v2 NSCLC, mTOR (damper delta_r=+0.049) killed more than MEK1 (anchor delta_r=-0.011) -- CONFIRMED. In CRC, MEK1 is the damper (delta_r=+0.120) and mTOR is the anchor (delta_r=-0.117). If H2 confirmed: SAME drug classes swap relative efficacy exactly as ODS predicts from topology. If H2 denied: mTOR has topology-independent efficacy that overrides structural position -- mTOR essentiality (essential anchor) dominates over structural damper assignment."
    }
